### @EnableMethodSecurity

Enable method-level security with `@EnableMethodSecurity` (modern) or `@EnableGlobalMethodSecurity` (legacy).

```java
@Configuration
@EnableMethodSecurity
public class MethodSecurityConfig {
    // Method security annotations are now active
}
```

### @PreAuthorize

The most flexible annotation. Uses SpEL expressions to control access before method execution.

```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/orders")
public class OrderController {

    @PreAuthorize("hasRole('ADMIN') or #order.userId == authentication.principal.id")
    @PostMapping
    public Order createOrder(@RequestBody Order order) {
        return orderService.save(order);
    }

    @PreAuthorize("hasAuthority('ORDER_READ')")
    @GetMapping("/{id}")
    public Order getOrder(@PathVariable Long id) {
        return orderService.findById(id);
    }
}
```

### @PostAuthorize

Evaluates after method execution. Can access the return value via the `returnObject` variable.

```java
@PostAuthorize("returnObject.ownerId == authentication.principal.id")
public Document getDocument(Long id) {
    return documentRepository.findById(id).orElse(null);
}
```

### @Secured and @RolesAllowed

Simpler alternatives that only check roles by name.

```java
@Secured("ROLE_ADMIN")
public void deleteUser(Long id) { ... }

@RolesAllowed({"USER", "ADMIN"})
public List<Item> getItems() { ... }
```

### SpEL Expressions

- `hasRole('ROLE')` - Checks if user has the given role
- `hasAuthority('AUTHORITY')` - Checks if user has the given authority
- `hasAnyRole('A', 'B')` - Checks multiple roles
- `#paramName` - References method parameters
- `authentication` - The current Authentication object

codeExample:
@Service
@EnableMethodSecurity
public class DocumentService {

    @PreAuthorize("hasRole('ADMIN') or #document.ownerId == authentication.principal.id")
    public Document updateDocument(@P("document") Document document) {
        return documentRepository.save(document);
    }

    @PreAuthorize("hasAuthority('DOCUMENT_DELETE')")
    @PostAuthorize("returnObject == null or returnObject.ownerId == authentication.principal.id")
    public Document deleteDocument(Long id) {
        Document doc = documentRepository.findById(id).orElse(null);
        if (doc != null) documentRepository.delete(doc);
        return doc;
    }

    @Secured("ROLE_ADMIN")
    public List<Document> getAllDocuments() {
        return documentRepository.findAll();
    }
}
